The invention provides the algorithm that a six-bit binary system is conversed into a four-bit six-bit binary system or a five-bit six-bit binary system and an uncompression algorithm. A pixel matrix is cut into pixel groups and reference matrixes corresponding to pixel positions in the pixel groups in a one-to-one mode are arranged, the last two bits or the last bit are or is judged to be matched with the reference matrixes for computing, and therefore the binary system color codes of pixels can be compressed. The byte length of red, green, blue (RGB) of binary codes can be shortened, storage spaces can be reduced, the size of a liquid crystal display (LCD) can be reduced, an integrated circuit (IC) can be driven beneficially, and manufacturing cost of circuit boards in the LCD can be reduced.
